[1] Case update
Date: Tue 3 Mar 2020
Source: CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola) [in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us3.campaign-archive.com/?u=b34a30571d429859fb249533d&id=76c94d6e4d


The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 2 Mar 2020
- Since the start of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3444, of which 3310 have been confirmed and 134 are probable. In total, have been 2264 deaths (2130 in confirmed and 134 in probable cases) and 1168 people have recovered or survived [3444 minus 2264 makes 1180. - Mod.SH];
- 386 suspected cases under investigation;
- no new confirmed cases for the 14th consecutive day;
- no new deaths among the confirmed cases;
- no new recoveries released from ETCs [Ebola treatment centers];
- no health workers are among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 167 (approximately 5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

News

The Ebola treatment center in Beni released on Tue 3 Mar 2020 the last confirmed Ebola patient.
- This is a 57 year-old woman from the Kanzulinzuli health area listed on 5 Feb 2020 as contact with her daughter, a nurse.
- She was followed and was vaccinated on 8 Feb 2020 before being discharged the same day as showing no signs of illness.
- Then she was returned to the Police Nationale Congolaise (PNC) cantonment site in Kanzulinzuli.
- She began to show signs on 13 Feb 2020, in particular by anorexia not reported to the community monitoring relay.
- From 14-16 Feb, she felt dizzy (14 Feb 2020), followed by nausea (15 Feb 2020), and headache, asthenia, cough, vomiting, and abdominal pain and diarrhea. She still had not reported to the contact tracking team, or to the PNC site duty nurse. Reasons why she hadn't taken anything as medicine.
- It was on 17 Feb 2020 that with the persistence of the signs rose and fever added and objectified that the lady had been the subject of an alert by the Community Relay. She was sent to the Beni Transit Center (CT) after validation as a suspect case, then the same day, to the Beni Ebola treatment center after confirmation of the Ebola virus disease (EVD).
- It is also good to know that initially 39 contacts were listed around this Ebola survivor.
- Note that this is the 1st time since the declaration by the Ministry of Health of the 10th epidemic of Ebola virus disease that all Ebola treatment centers are empty of confirmed cases of this disease. To date, therefore, there have been zero confirmed cases of Ebola in the Democratic Republic of the Congo.
- The 10th epidemic began on 1 Aug 2018 in Mangina in the Mabalako health zone in the territory of Beni in North Kivu province and spread to the provinces of South Kivu and Ituri in practically 28 other health zones for all 3 provinces.

Vaccination
-----------
- As of 29 Feb 2020, 20 339 people have been vaccinated with the 2nd vaccine Ad26.ZEBOV/MVA-BN-Filo (Johnson & Johnson) in the 2 health areas from Karisimbi and Goma.
- Since the start of vaccination on 08 Aug 2018, 299 330 people have been vaccinated with the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine.

Monitoring at entry points
--------------------------
- Since the start of the epidemic, the total number of travelers checked (temperature measurement) at health checkpoints, until 29 Feb 2020, is 157 200 341;
- to date, a total of 109 entry points (PoE) and health control points (PoC) have been established in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri in order to protect the country's major cities and avoid the spread of the epidemic in neighboring countries.

